review.reviewBody: The bola bola steamed bun and ube ensaymada are very good. Prices are good too.

The three different Hopia pastries were great. Price is fair. There is an issue with the Hopia ordering though in that there's an extra $1.25 charge on it because that's the base price, which you then add $1.25 for each flavor you want included. The people processing the order tried to fix this but ended up the order was still not entirely correct - it was supposed to have 12 Hopia (3 orders with all flavors checked means 3 x 4) but I only received 11. I think they should just put each Hopia flavor on the menu as a separate item rather than combining them all together into one.
Delicious but portion is quite small for the price
